ther.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FromTheMouthsOfBabes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FromTheMouthsOfBabes">From the Mouths of Babes</a>: In Episode 9 of Season 2, Maria talks about Kodaka and Sena <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> getting married</span>, and thinks nothing of it other than its a good thing. The other girls, however, aren't too pleased about hearing that <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhamLine" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhamLine">Wham Line</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FrothyMugsOfWater" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FrothyMugsOfWater">Frothy Mugs of Water</a>: In the light novel series, Pegasus offers Kodaka wine when he visits for the night, and Kodaka <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CantHoldHisLiquor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CantHoldHisLiquor">proceeds to drink him under the table</a>. In the TV series, Kodaka is given non-alcoholic grape juice instead... or at least that is what Pegasus claims, because it's still clearly wine and Kodaka still gets (a little) drunk from it.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FartsOnFire" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FartsOnFire">Farts on Fire</a>: Another one of Kobato's old hobbies was to lighting her farts on fire. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationDistillation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationDistillation">This was also not mentioned in the anime.</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GagBoobs" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GagBoobs">Gag Boobs</a>: The anime drives the point home by focusing many a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MaleGaze" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MaleGaze">Male Gaze</a> towards Sena's big breasts.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GamerChick" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Game